----- stdout -----
Explain why a module depends on another module

Usage: crawk why [OPTIONS] <SOURCE> <TARGET>

Arguments:
  <SOURCE>  Source module that depends on TARGET (e.g., "analyzer" or "parser::visitor")
  <TARGET>  Target module being depended on (e.g., "reference" or "discover::module_tree")

Options:
  -r, --recursive        Recursively include SOURCE's submodules (disabled by default)
  -t, --include-tests    Include modules defined in `#[cfg(test)]` blocks (excluded by default)
  -f, --format <FORMAT>  Output format [default: plain] [possible values: plain, grouped]
  -h, --help             Print help (see more with '--help')

----- stderr -----
